"Well, gotta wait for the bus to get here, so let's stop off at WB and grab a pint or two, eh?  This one pours a murky ruby-sienna topped by a finger of glowing off-white foam.  The nose comprises maple syrup backed by mild pine resin and mixed greens.  The taste turns the tables, leading with the pine-led greens and backing up with the maple syrup.  The body is a light medium, with a light moderate carbonation and a drying finish.  Overall, this isn't a bad brown, really, but I, for one, feel the overt hoppiness hurts things in general.  I won't have another of these, as far as I can see, but I also won't dissuade someone from having one, either."
